<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1953-08-11T08:30:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1953-08-11T08:30:00-05:00" n="780" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d780">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">690D.91/8–1153: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in India</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_AGV1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Allen</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss></hi><note n="1" xml:id="d780fn1">This telegram was repeated for information to
                                    Karachi and London.</note></head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left"><hi rend="smallcaps">restricted<lb/>priority</hi></seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">New
                                            Delhi</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1953-08-11T19:00:00+05:30">August 11, 1953—7
                                        p.m.</date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>295. During conversation with <persName corresp="#p_PSNR1">Pillai</persName> today I mentioned rumors of American
                                interference in Kashmir and said that while I took no official
                                cognizance of them, since there had been no allegation of such
                                interference by <gloss target="#t_GOI1">GOI</gloss>, I was anxious
                                to find out their source. I said I felt confident <gloss target="#t_GOI1">GOI</gloss> was as desirous as I was to clear
                                up situation and I would welcome any evidence it might have on
                                subject.</p>
                            <pb facs="0279" n="1329" xml:id="pg_1329"/>
                            <p><persName corresp="#p_PSNR1">Pillai</persName> said he wished to
                                assure me he personally did not believe one word of these rumors,
                                and he would let me have any information he might receive on
                                subject. I emphasized that any basis whatever for reports that US
                                had offered loans to <persName corresp="#p_ASM1">Abdullah</persName>
                                would be especially welcome.</p>
                            <closer><signed><persName corresp="#p_AGV1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Allen</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>